              <g class="proof-phone">
                <rect x="240" y="40" width="40" height="68" rx="5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" class="text-ink-2"/>
                <rect x="244" y="46" width="32" height="50" rx="1" fill="currentColor" class="text-bg-3"/>
                <g class="proof-check" opacity="0">
                  <path d="M252 71 L258 77 L268 65" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-ember"/>
                </g>
                <g class="proof-spinner">
                  <circle cx="260" cy="71" r="6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" stroke-dasharray="9 28" class="text-ember"/>
                </g>
                <rect x="252" y="100" width="16" height="2" rx="1" fill="currentColor" class="text-ink-3"/>
                <text x="260" y="130" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" class="text-ember" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="6.5" letter-spacing="1">50–200 MS</text>
                <text x="260" y="142" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" class="text-ink-4" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="5.5" letter-spacing="1.2">CONSUMER PHONE</text>
              </g>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 md:p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center gap-6 lg:border-l border-rule-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-medium leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.025em]" style="font-size:clamp(26px,2.6vw,38px)">
            <span class="block font-light text-ink-2">Verified</span>
            on a phone.
          </h3>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-2">
            <div class="border-l-2 border-ink-4 pl-4">
              <span class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-3 mb-2">Most chains</span>
              <p class="text-[13.5px] leading-[1.55] text-ink-2">To verify the chain, you run a full node — gigabytes of state, hours to sync. Or you trust a hosted RPC. Either way, verification is gated by infrastructure.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-2 border-ember pl-4">
              <span class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ember mb-2">Adamant</span>
              <p class="text-[13.5px] leading-[1.55] text-ink">Validators generate a Halo 2 recursive proof at every epoch boundary. Each epoch's proof verifies the prior epoch's proof plus all per-tx proofs in this epoch. The total proof at any point is one ~5–10 KB artifact verifying the entire chain. Verification: 50–200ms on a smartphone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3 pt-5 border-t border-rule font-mono text-[10.5px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">
            <span class="text-ink-2">→ Property delivered:</span>
            <span class="text-ember">Phone-verifiable</span>
            <span class="text-ink-4">·</span>
            <span class="text-ember">No light-client trust</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ────── MECHANISM 04: CONSTITUTIONAL IMMUTABILITY ────── -->
      <div class="mechanism border-b border-rule-2 grid lg:grid-cols-2" data-reveal>
        <div class="lg:order-2 bg-bg-2 p-8 md:p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center min-h-[420px]">
          <div class="mb-6 flex items-baseline justify-between gap-3">
            <span class="font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-ember">MECHANISM 04 · GOVERNANCE</span>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-4">WP §11</span>
          </div>
          <div class="immut-viz relative h-[220px] -mx-2">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 320 180" class="block w-full h-full" aria-hidden="true">
              <!-- Locked rules core -->
              <g class="immut-core">
                <rect x="125" y="65" width="70" height="50" rx="3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2" class="text-ember"/>
                <!-- Padlock body -->
                <rect x="153" y="82" width="14" height="11" rx="1.5" fill="currentColor" class="text-ember"/>
                <!-- Padlock shackle -->
                <path d="M156 82 L156 78 Q156 74 160 74 Q164 74 164 78 L164 82" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" class="text-ember"/>
                <text x="160" y="105" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" class="text-ember" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="5" letter-spacing="0.8">GENESIS RULES</text>
                <text x="160" y="135" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" class="text-ink-4" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="6.5" letter-spacing="1" class="text-ink-3">FIXED · NO ADMIN</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Validators arranged around the core, each with their own pulse delay -->
              <g class="immut-validators" fill="currentColor" class="text-cold">
                <!-- Top row -->
                <circle cx="60" cy="40" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:0s"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="32" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:0.4s"/>
                <circle cx="160" cy="28" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:0.8s"/>
                <circle cx="220" cy="32" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:1.2s"/>
                <circle cx="260" cy="40" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:1.6s"/>
                <!-- Bottom row -->
                <circle cx="60" cy="140" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:2.0s"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="148" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:2.4s"/>
                <circle cx="220" cy="148" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:2.8s"/>
                <circle cx="260" cy="140" r="4" class="immut-validator" style="animation-delay:3.2s"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Subtle radiating circles to suggest sovereignty -->
              <g class="immut-radiate" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" class="text-ember" opacity="0.18">
                <circle cx="160" cy="90" r="55" stroke-width="0.5"/>
                <circle cx="160" cy="90" r="80" stroke-width="0.4"/>
              </g>

              <text x="160" y="172" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" class="text-ink-4" font-family="JetBrains Mono, monospace" font-size="6.5" letter-spacing="1.2">EACH NODE OPERATOR · INDEPENDENT</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:order-1 p-8 md:p-12 lg:p-16 flex flex-col justify-center gap-6 lg:border-r border-rule-2">
          <h3 class="font-display font-medium leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.025em]" style="font-size:clamp(26px,2.6vw,38px)">
            <span class="block font-light text-ink-2">No master.</span>
            No off switch.
          </h3>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-2">
            <div class="border-l-2 border-ink-4 pl-4">
              <span class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ink-3 mb-2">Most chains</span>
              <p class="text-[13.5px] leading-[1.55] text-ink-2">A foundation, multisig, or token-holder vote can change consensus rules, gas costs, issuance, or system contracts. The capability is permanent once established.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="border-l-2 border-ember pl-4">
              <span class="block font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-ember mb-2">Adamant</span>
              <p class="text-[13.5px] leading-[1.55] text-ink">No on-chain governance. No admin keys. No upgrade authority. Change requires a published spec, a public reference implementation, and 2/3+1-by-stake of validators each independently choosing to run new software. Validators who don't upgrade either stay on the existing chain or migrate voluntarily.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3 pt-5 border-t border-rule font-mono text-[10.5px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-ink-3">
            <span class="text-ink-2">→ Property delivered:</span>
            <span class="text-ember">Credibly neutral</span>
            <span class="text-ink-4">·</span>
            <span class="text-ember">Capture-resistant</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Connect-the-dots summary -->
      <div class="mt-px bg-bg-2 border border-rule-2 border-t-0 px-8 md:px-12 lg:px-16 py-10 md:py-12" data-reveal>
        <p class="max-w-[68ch] mx-auto text-center font-display text-[18px] md:text-[22px] leading-[1.4] tracking-[-0.015em] text-ink-2">
          <span class="text-ink">Each mechanism solves one of the seven gaps.</span>
          Together, they deliver every property no other chain has combined.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───────── §03 / WHERE WE ARE ───────── -->
  <section class="border-t border-rule">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <span class="num">§03 / WHERE WE ARE</span>
          <h2><span class="light">Specification phase.</span>No token. No timeline.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="desc">
          Adamant is a draft specification. There is no chain running yet. There is no token to buy. There is no allocation. This page exists to document the design and let people follow progress.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-px bg-rule-2 border border-rule-2">
        <div class="bg-bg-2 p-8 md:p-12 flex flex-col gap-4 min-h-[260px] card-hover" data-reveal>
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-ember">PHASE 01 · CURRENT</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[24px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.02em]">Specification</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-2">Whitepaper draft v0.1. Public for review and comment. Cryptographic primitives selected; consensus model documented; genesis mechanism defined.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-bg-2 p-8 md:p-12 flex flex-col gap-4 min-h-[260px] card-hover" data-reveal style="transition-delay:80ms">
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-ink-3">PHASE 02 · NEXT</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[24px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink-2">Reference implementation</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-3">Rust implementation, Apache 2.0. Public from the first commit. No private fork, no closed beta.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-bg-2 p-8 md:p-12 flex flex-col gap-4 min-h-[260px] card-hover" data-reveal style="transition-delay:160ms">
          <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-ink-3">PHASE 03 · LATER</span>
          <h3 class="font-display text-[22px] md:text-[24px] font-semibold leading-[1.15] tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink-2">Public testnet · audits · genesis</h3>
          <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.65] text-ink-3">Testnet open to anyone. Independent audits before mainnet. Genesis only when the work is ready.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ───────── MANIFESTO ───────── -->
